subSubSection.paragraph:
The wood of 

Scolopia hazomby

is used for the manufacture of boards and railroad ties (
Ratovoson et al. 318; Service Forestier 14740, 21782, 26659
) and for heating and charcoal (
Service Forestier 14740
). Leaves are used to treat stomachache (
Cours 4049
). The fruit is eaten by lemurs (
Overdorff 34
).

